parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning OCS sensor can cause the passenger airbag warning light to flash or remain on, indicating that the passenger airbag may not deploy in the event of a crash, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The passenger airbag warning light flashes or remains on
the passenger airbag is disabled
the light turns on and off intermittently
the sensor fails to detect occupants correctly
the system fails to reset after attempts to correct the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracks in the dashboard can lead to aesthetic and functional issues, potentially affecting the overall safety and performance of the vehicle.
symptoms: Cracks appear on the dashboard
the cracks spread over time
the dashboard becomes brittle and prone to further damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering lock box can prevent the vehicle from starting, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing safety issues.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
no warning indicators are illuminated
the steering lock box needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty OCS sensor can cause the passenger airbag to be suppressed, which can fail to provide adequate protection in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is flashing non-stop
the passenger airbag may not deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Transmission Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates forward when shifted into reverse
the vehicle accelerates without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle fails to respond to braking inputs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Aluminum Locking Nut/Sleeve for TPMS Valve Stem
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the aluminum locking nut/sleeve for the TPMS valve stem can cause the valve stem to detach, leading to tire pressure monitoring system failure, and potentially resulting in tire blowouts, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Tire blowout
loss of tire pressure
TPMS warning light illumination
valve stem detachment
corrosion or cracking of the aluminum locking nut/sleeve.
